27/12/2009
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- A bomb was hurled at a car belonging to the Serbian Education Ministry early Friday (December 25th) in Mitrovica. 
No one was injured. 
According to local deputy police chief Ergin Medic, the target of the attack was a Zastava 128 with Serbian registration plates that was parked in a family's yard. 
Friday's attack was the second in the Serb-dominated northern part of divided Mitrovica in 24 hours. 
(Netpress, Tanjug, B92 - 25/12/09)
